<unclassified>
A DRUNKEN sailor was jailed for six months yesterday for falling asleep on watch after a whisky binge.

Polish chief officer Jerzy Pawluk, 42, admitted endangering his 200ft ship and letting it run into the coast near Montrose, Scotland, last December.

Newcastle Judge Denis Orde said: 'It could have been wholesale slaughter.'

